casebody.data:
Kucharek, a.k.a. Kucherak, Appellant, v. Tri-City Family Medicine, Inc. et al., Appellees.

[Cite as Kucharek v. Tri-City Family Medicine, Inc., 96 Ohio St.3d 1202, 2002-Ohio-3454.]

(No. 2001-1002 Submitted May 22, 2002 Decided July 17, 2002.) Spangenberg, Shibley & Liber, L.L.P., Justin F. Madden and Mary A. Cavanaugh, for appellant. Reminger & Reminger Co., L.P.A., and Martin T. Galvin, for appellees.

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur. Pfeifer, J., dissents and would reverse the judgment of the court of appeals.
